        <num>CC 1309</num>
        <heading>1309.  Partition between possessors in common</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1309.  Partition between possessors in common.
It is not indispensable to be owner in common in order to be able to support the action of partition; possession alone, when it is lawful and proceeds from a just title, will support it.
Thus, usufructuaries of the same estate can institute among themselves the action of partition.</p>
        </content>
